<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Rupee Weakens Further Against US Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Indian rupee weakened
further against the US dollar and closed sharply lower at 35.65/67
rupees per dollar at the interbank foreign exchange market in
Mumbai (Bombay) today.
</P>
<P>
Opening easier at 35.60/63 rupees compared to the overnight
finish of 35.58/61 rupees, the rupee gradually dropped to 35.66/68
on steady commercial dollar buying by corporations and importers.
</P>
<P>
After the rupee attempted a smart rally to 35.58/60 rupees on
fresh dollar sales, the State Bank of India started to heavily bid
the greenback. As a result of the buying, the rupee again fell and
settled at 35.65/67 rupees per dollar at the end of trading hours.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
