<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian Labor Income Up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Overall wages and salaries in
Canada rose by 0.2 percent in May, the second consecutive monthly
increase, Statistics Canada reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The May rise stemmed increases in these areas: transportation,
storage, communications and other utilities, finance, insurance,
real estate, mining, quarrying and oil wells, and health and
social services.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, pay decreases were noted in construction and
commercial and personal services, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Despite fluctuations, overall growth in wages and salaries in
the first five months of 1996 was 2.4 percent higher than in the
same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
