<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Up in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany's unemployment rate rose to
10.2 percent in July compared with 9.9 percent in June, the
Federal Labor Office reported today.
</P>
<P>
The jobless totaled nearly four million in July, which meant
127,000 people lost their jobs that month, Labor Office head
Bernhard Jagoda told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Jagoda said the figure made the situation in the German labor
market appear worse than it was.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the increased unemployment partially to factors
such as the release of holiday labor as well and fewer hirings
than usual during the holiday period.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate in Germany hit a record high of 11.1
percent last February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
