<HEADLINE> Egyptian, American Businessmen to Finance 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian and American businessmen
will jointly finance 10 giant projects in Egypt, The Egyptian
Gazette reported today.
</P>
<P>
The 10 projects, in the fields of industry, tourism,
electricity and land reclamation, are expected to push forward
Egypt's economic development and create more jobs, the
English-language newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Among the projects is the establishment of a free trade zone
north of the Gulf of Suez, the paper said, adding that exports
from the zone will be exempt from taxes.
</P>
<P>
Another project is for producing aluminum with an estimated
investment of 170 to 200 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
