<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hongkong Gold Medalist to Get Hero's Welcome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONGKONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong will throw a hero's VIP
treatment to welcome home its first ever Olympic medal winner Lee
Lai-shan from Atlanta, according to local reports.
</P>
<P>
Lee Lai-shan, who won the gold medal in women's windsurfing,
claimed the first victory for Hongkong since the colony began
competing in the Olympic Games 44 years ago. The Atlanta Games
marked the last time Hong Kong would compete under British rule.
</P>
<P>
On stepping off the plane on Wednesday, the 25-year-old Lee
will be whisked away into a motorcade that will parade her down a
street, appropriately named Olympic Avenue, to meet thousands of
her fans at the Hong Kong Cultural Center.
</P>
<P>
She then will board a ferry that will take her and her family
to their home in Cheung Chau, an outer island some 30 minutes from
Hongkong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
