<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- A newly-signed United States bill providing for
sanctions against new investments in the oil industries of Iran
and Libya is not going " in the right direction", an official of
the European Union (EU) said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Some 50,000 people in the Japanese city of Hiroshima
gathered today at the city's Peace Memorial Park to commemorate
the victims of the atomic bomb attack 51 years ago and pray for
peace with a series of ceremonies, Kyodo News said.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin narrowly
escaped an explosion which rocked western Moscow this morning as
his car was only three minutes' drive from the scene.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Tens of thousands of Romans gathered at a grand rally
on Monday evening to commemorate their fellow patriots gassed down
by German fascists in 1944 and protest the release of a former SS
captain who admitted taking part in the massacre.
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japanese government officials finally responded today
to the appeals of medical experts to declare the two-month-old
food poisoning outbreak an infectious disease.
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The Guatemalan government and guerrillas started
a new round of negotiations here today for a peace agreement to
end the 36-year civil war in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
