<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Ostrich Exports to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's commercial ostrich
producers expect earnings worth at least 8.9 million U.S. Dollars
from sales for the year ended this July.
</P>
<P>
Chief executive of the Ostrich Producers Association of
Zimbabwe (TOPAZ) Phil Haxen said today the sales figures were an
improvement on the previous year's but he did not give further
details.
</P>
<P>
''There has for the last couple of years been an insatiable
demand for ostrich meat from Europe which with our current small
production cannot hope to satisfy,'' said Haxen.
</P>
<P>
Haxen said a slight increase in demand for ostrich meat is
expected in Europe as many people switched from beef following
health scares over the ''mad cow'' disease outbreak at the end of
last year.
</P>
<P>
''It's hoped the effect on ostrich meat prices will be
positive, but early indications are that the increase will be
modest. Prices will not double overnight,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe is one of the major exporters of ostriches to Europe
where ostrich meat is fast-gaining popularity because of its low
cholesterol levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
