<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Israeli Soldier Killed in S. Lebanon in Hezbollah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 6 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli soldiers was
killed and two others wounded today in an attack by Hezbollah
guerillas in south Lebanon, Israeli Army announced.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place in Barrachit, east of Kiryat Shemona, in
the central sector of Israeli self-claimed security zone.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah forces attacked an Israeli military position with
anti-tank rockets and mortars, killing one soldier and slightly
wounding two others, the army said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli forces retaliated immediately with tanks and artillery
fires, shelling suspected Hezbollah targets, it added.
</P>
<P>
This is the second attack by Hezbollah forces in the same area
in the past two days.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, two Israeli soldiers were wounded, one seriously,
after Hezbollah guerillas pounded an Israeli position at dawn with
mortar shells, machine guns and rocket-propelled grenades.
</P>
<P>
Israeli forces also responded with shelling suspected Hezbollah
 hideouts in the villages facing the security zone. No casualties
were reported.
</P>
<P>
Today's attack is the latest of a week of intensive
confrontations, during which the Israeli Army said that over 10
Hezbollah gunmen had been killed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hezbollah forces on Sunday night abducted a South
Lebanese Army (SLA) soldier from his home in south Lebanon.
Both the SLA and Israel have demanded his immediate return.
</P>
</TEXT>
