<HEADLINE> Czech Athlete Sells Olympic Medals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Czech canoeist Lukas Pollert has
sold his gold and silver medals won at the last two Olympic Games
after criticising the over-commercialization of the Olympic
movement, local media reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Czech CTK agency said the silver medal Pollert sold was won
in the Canadian canoe singles at Atlanta and the gold came from
the 1992 Barcelona Games.
</P>
