<HEADLINE> Mandela Calls for Improvement of Children's Lives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela today called on all sectors of society to assist
the government's drive to improve the lives of children.
</P>
<P>
In a luncheon held at the presidential residence in capital
Pretoria to welcome Lesotho's Queen Mother Mamohato, Mandela said
children are the country's future and therefore deserve to be
nurtured by society with love and care.
</P>
<P>
Too many African children still lack basic rights such as
shelter, healthy living conditions, education and medical
facilities, said Mandela.
</P>
<P>
Queen Mamohato, the widow of Lesotho's late King Moshoeshoe II
and mother of Monarch King Letsie III, arrived in South Africa
earlier today for a two-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Queen Mamohato is a patron of numerous children's
organizations in Lesotho, Mandela said South Africa and Lesotho
could work together to improve the lives of children. 
</P>
