<HEADLINE> Tanzania Seeks Kenya's Backing in Its Coop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Tanzanian officials
today sought support from the Kenyan government for their own
cooperative movement.
</P>
<P>
The 12-member Tanzanian delegation, led by Chairman of Western
Zone Tobacco Cooperative Daudi Juma, particularly appealed for
advice from Kenya on how to start their cooperative bank.
</P>
<P>
After years of experiments, cooperative societies in Tanzania
are still "in the initial stages", according to Juma who blamed
commercial banks for extorting high interest rates on loans.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian officials, having paid visits to Kenya's
cooperatives, said they were "very impressed" by the success of
the cooperative movement in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian team is expected to attend lectures at Nairobi's
College of Cooperative and conduct study tours in Kenya's Eastern
and Western Provinces. 
