multi-party democracy in Zanzibar is not normal. The two parties
should agree to iron out the differences together," Chief
Anyaoku added.
</P>
<P>
Chief Anyaoku, who ended his three-day visit to Zanzibar
yeasterday, said he was planning to hold further talks with Amour
and Hamad before departure, saying he was hopeful that the two
sides would eventually solve the tension.
</P>
<P>
