President Benjamin Mkapa, prime minister Frederick Sumaye,
Speaker of parliament Pius Msekwa and opposition leader in the
House Fatma Maghimbi in Dodoma.
</P>
<P>
Referring to mult-party democracy in Tanzania, the
Commonwealth boss said: "Not all countries have been as fortunate
as Tanzania in usheing in multi-party democracy peacefully. You
have been able to complete the transition with far less headache
than many countries."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chief Anyaoku called on Tanzania's small and
medium- scale industiries to draw from the Commonwealth Fund
which had been launched recently in Harare of Zimbabwe with an
aim to promote industrial development in Commonwealth countries.
