<HEADLINE> EU Aid for Swedish Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brussels, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
provide Sweden with ECU 17 million (one ECU equals about 1.3 US$)
to improve the competitiveness of its small and medium-sized
enterprises(SMEs).
</P>
<P>
The aid, which comes from the European Union's structural
funds, will be funded to SMEs in Sweden's sparsely populated,
rural and declining industrial areas, the European Commission said
today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Commission, another ECU 17 million from the
Swedish authorities and ECU 14 million from the country's private
sector would also be injected into the SMEs, pushing the total
investment to ECU 48 million.
</P>
<P>
The investment is expected to help create 5,200 new jobs, train
20,000 employees and increase sales by 20 percent for 4,600
enterprises.It is also expected to put 3,000 others into new
markets.
</P>
<P>
SMEs with less than 50 staff account for 99 percent of all
Swedish enterprises and have been the main source of job creation
in recent years. Between 1992 and 1994, some 44,000 new jobs were
created in enterprises with less than 10 employees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
