<HEADLINE> Construction on Steel Production Line In Guangzhou Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Work to build a large
thin-plate continuous cast and continuous roll project has begun
in the capital city of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The new Zhujiang Iron and Steel Co. Ltd. will invest more than
600 million US dollars in its first-phase project, importing the
first such production line from Germany.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion of the project in 1998, the company will be
able to produce 150 tons of hot-roll or cold-roll steel plate.
</P>
<P>
The thin plate is an essential component of containers, steel
tubing, household appliances, vehicles, motorcycles, ships, and
light industrial products.
</P>
<P>
Light industry is doing well in Guangdong Province, especially
in the Pearl River Delta, but a large quantity of thin steel plate
has to be imported.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on this type of plant was signed between China and
Germany when Premier Li Peng visited Germany in July, 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Zhujiang company is one of the major enterprises of the
Guangzhou Iron and Steel Group Company.
</P>
<P>
When the new plant goes into production, the entire group will
be able to turn out two million tons of steel a year, and its
annual sales will grow from 1995's 3.3 billion yuan to ten
billion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
