<HEADLINE> Harbin Benefitting From Industrial Adjustments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- This industrial city of northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province has made an effort in the past few
years to improve its industry and GDP and financial revenues rose
11.3 percent and 26.1 percent, respectively, in the first half of
this year.
</P>
<P>
The city began adjusting its industrial structure in 1991, in a
move to allocate more funds and resources for better industries
and to develop more competitive products.
</P>
<P>
Five pillar industries - power generating equipment, measuring
apparatuses and instruments, small and mid-sized bearings,
pharmaceuticals, and flax - have taken shape, producing 48 percent
of the city's total industrial output value.
</P>
<P>
The improved technical content and equipment contributed 35
percent to the city's economic growth by the end of the Eighth
Five-Year Plan (1991-1995), as against 25 percent at the end of
the Seventh Five-Year Plan (1986-1990). 
</P>
