<HEADLINE> Price Index in Service Sector Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The rapid rise in commodity
prices in China's tertiary industry has been curbed, according to
a release from the State Statistics Bureau today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that housing costs and related service fees
rose by 11.5 percent and 15.7 percent respectively in the first
half of the year, compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The major price increases were in transportation fees, which
have risen by 17.8 percent, housing rent, up 39 percent, water,
electricity, and gas, up 12.6 percent, and school expenditure,
19.1 percent, from the same period in 1995.
</P>
<P>
After a sharp rise in the first quarter, commodity prices in
the service sector are now increasing by a smaller amount,
according to the study. 
