<P>
Lohani, while answering lawmakers' questions here at the lower
house, said that the new route to the Bangladeshi port city of
Chittagong via eastern India's Phulbari was chosen as an
alternative to a former route during Nepali Prime Minister Sher
Bahadur Deuba's visit to India last February.
</P>
<P>
The former route through India's Radhikapur was found
unsuitable due to various reasons, he said.
</P>
<P>
As a mountainous country, Nepal heavily depends on the southern
neighbor India for the transit of its imports and exports.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
