<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia opposes the United
States' move punishing foreign companies investing in Iran and
Libya because this is against the principle of sovereignty,
Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said here today.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on US President Bill Clinton's signing last Monday
of a bill aimed at punishing foreign companies investing in the
two countries, the minister said Malaysia would not accept the US
decision because as a sovereign country Malaysia had the right to
decide what was best for itself.
