<HEADLINE> Dinosaur Stamps on Display </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Sun Longchun, vice-minister of
public health, held a show of more than 600 dinosaur stamps at
Geoexpo '96 at the 30th International Geological Congress here.
</P>
<P>
The dinosaur stamps are from 60 countries. Sun, who worked in
geology for several decades, said that he hoped to get more stamps
from colleagues in geology worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The stamps have aroused the interest of visitors. Linda C. Kah,
a geologist from the United States, said that she has a set of
four dinosaur stamps, and that the exhibition is "simply
wonderful."  
</P>
</TEXT>
