<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World-travelling Bicyclist Reaches Azerbaijan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Hady Cusvojo, an Indonesian man
bicycling around the world, reached Baku, the capital of the
Azerbaijan Republic on Wednesday, according to reports from
Moscow.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Indonesian set off on a trip around the world
by bicycle on August 17, 1990, which marked the Independence Day
of Indonesia, and he has ever since covered 40 more countries.
</P>
<P>
The next stop of his world-travelling journey on his bike is
other Central Asian countries, afterwards he will be touring Japan
and the United States.
</P>
<P>
He schedules to end his ambitious trip on the bicycle across
the world by May, 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
