<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Increased Overseas Investment In Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The capital of central China's
Hubei Province, Wuhan, added 187 foreign-funded projects during
the first half of the year, with overseas contractual investment
reaching 170 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
This year, 48 percent of overseas investment came from European
countries, the United States, and Japan, more than that from Hong
Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Seventy percent of those who came to the city looking for
investment opportunities this year are from Europe, the United
States, and Japan, 30 percent more than for the same period in
1995.
</P>
<P>
The number of new production-related projects this year rose 29
percent over 1995. More than 90 percent of 12 new foreign-funded
projects with investment surpassing five million US dollars each
this year are involved in production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
