<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ilhwa Chunma Wins Asian Super Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Sin Tae-Youg scored the winning
header to pace Asian club champions Ilhwa Chunma of South Korea to
a 1-0 win over hosts Bellmare Hiratsuka and snatch the Asian Super
Cup in Hiratsuka, Japan on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sin muscled in the header in the 77th minute when forward Ko
Jeong-Woon dribbled through from the right before putting a high
pass into the center.
</P>
<P>
Asian Cup Winners Cup holders Bellmare, who needed to beat the
South Koreans by more than two goals to win the title, fought
aggressively from the outset. They unleashed 17 shots on goal
against Ilhwa's seven, but found no chance to penetrate the
visitors' tight defence.
</P>
<P>
In the first game in South Korea a week ago, Ilhwa defeated
Bellmare 5-3.
</P>
<P>
It was the first victory in the Asian Super Cup for
Ilhwa. Yokohama Flugels of Japan won the inaugural title last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
