<HEADLINE> Communist Party of India Elects New leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Ardhendu Bhushan Bardhan,
deputy general secretary of the Communist Party of India (CPI),
today took over as the general secretary of the party in place of
Indrajit Gupta, the Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
Gupta became home minister in June in the United Front
government led by Prime Minister H.D. Deve Gowda.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, N. Giri Prasad was unanimously elected the deputy
general secretary of the party at its National Council meeting
held here. 
</P>
