<HEADLINE> Nestle Donates Milk For Flood-Stricken Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Nestle (China) Investment
Services Ltd. donated one million yuan worth of sweetened
condensed milk in response to disaster relief efforts of the
Ministry of Civil Affairs for people in southern China who were
affected by severe flooding.
</P>
<P>
Fan Baojun, vice-minister of civil affairs, expressed gratitude
on behalf of the people in flood-stricken areas at a ceremony and
said that the company will soon transport the supplies to Hunan,
Hubei, Anhui, Jiangxi and other flood-stricken provinces.
</P>
<P>
"Nestle has a long-term commitment to China," T. Klauser, CEO
of Nestle (China) Investment Services Ltd., said, "It is committed
to serving the interests of the Chinese people by providing good
quality products at affordable prices."
</P>
<P>
Nestle (China) Investment Services, which recently opened in
Beijing, is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Nestle S.A. of
Switzerland. Nestle has 10 joint ventures and two wholly-owned
companies in China with a total investment of some three billion
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960807.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Supports Regional Trade Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari said here today that Pakistan supports all development
projects and trade cooperation among the countries of South Asia,
Middle East and the Central Asian Republics.
</P>
<P>
Leghari made this remarks today while talking with Boris
Shikhmuradov, the visiting Foreign Minister and Deputy Prime
Minister of Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
The President said that though Pakistan provides the easiest
and the shortest land route between the Central Asian Republics
and the sea, "we would welcome any other routes or links which
benefit the 300 million people of the region."
</P>
<P>
He said that the whole region has huge natural resources as
well as very big consumers' markets.
</P>
<P>
"The region can have a system of several pipelines to cater to
the ever growing needs of gas, oil and other items in Pakistan,
India and other regional countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Pakistan is looking forward to effective
implementation of all such projects.
</P>
<P>
He also said Pakistan would be willing to provide machinery,
cement and sugar plants to Turkmenistan and that Pakistani labor
could be employed for the proposed oil and gas pipelines between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He observed that economic and political stability in the
Central Asia Republics was the best guarantee for peace and
development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Shikhmuradov fully agreed with Leghari, saying Turkmenistan and
Pakistan have very close identity of views and there is tremendous
goodwill among the peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Turkmenistan wants to have very close
cooperation with Pakistan and other countries in this region. "we
could all benefit from each other's huge resources and big
markets," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960807.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Mineral Deposit Discoveries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China's mineral, oil and natural
gas discoveries over the past five years have been significant.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the Ministry of Geology and
Mineral Resources, more than 500 gold, silver, copper, rare earth
and other scarce mineral deposits useful for economic development
have been found over the past five years. They include 200 gold
mines and 38 silver mines.
</P>
<P>
The discovery of five oil and gas fields on the northern part
of the Tarim Basin, in northwest China, and two others in the
western part of the Tarim suggests that the region has good
prospects for oil and gas production.
</P>
<P>
A number of high-yield oil and gas wells have been dug in the
East China Sea with total reserves of 2.3 million tons of oil and
19 billion cubic meters of gas.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the Chunxiao-1 oil well started its trial run,
producing 1.6 million cubic meters of gas and 200 cubic meters of
oil a day.
</P>
<P>
A geological survey in Tibet and in the Badain Jaran Desert in
the western part of the Inner Mongolian Plateau, has shown signs
of oil and gas reserve.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chinese geologists have completed regional surveys
in various parts of China, giving them a clear idea about the
distribution of underground water and the state of geological
disasters.
</P>
<P>
Geologists have also conducted hydrologic and environmental
surveys on 150 state key projects, including the Three Gorges
Project on the Yangtze River.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
