<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clearance of Land Mines in Afghanistan in Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- About 13,000 square meters'
land in western Kabul has been cleared of land mines, said Radio
Kabul which was monitored here today.
</P>
<P>
The radio said that a special campaign was launched by some
organizations in different areas of the country to clear land from
mines and explosives on humanitarian ground.
</P>
<P>
It may be mentioned that thousands of people including children
have lost their limbs and other parts of bodies in the land mines'
explosions in recent years, the radio added.
</P>
<P>
Afghanistan, which has suffered from 16 years of war, is one of
the world's biggest land-mine zones now.  
</P>
</TEXT>
