<HEADLINE> 24 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-four rebels of the illegal
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the clashes with
Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey, according to a
statement from the governor's office of the emergency rule region.
</P>
<P>
The statement said today that the security forces wiped out
nine PKK rebels in military operations in Baskale town in Van
province, seven in Semdinli and Yuksekova towns in Hakkari
province, four near Palu town in Elazig province, two in Hizan
town in Bitlis province and two in Idil town in Sirnak province.
</P>
<P>
