the provinces of Diyarbakir and Van.
</P>
<P>
More than 21,000 people including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops have been killed in clashes between the PKK and
security forces since the outlawed group started fighting for
self-rule in southeastern Turkey in August 1984. 
