<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Finding the proper shoes has
been a big problem for eight members of a large family in
southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region -- because they
were born without a heel on their feet.
</P>
<P>
Whenever they put on shoes, they have had to tie the shoes to
their feet because their heel bones are straight, making it seem
as if they have no heel.
</P>
<P>
Walking is quite difficult for the eight He family members in
Li'ao Village of Nandan County, because of the short soles.
</P>
<P>
He Jinxiu, a family member of the second generation, said that
it is a hereditary disease but gave no detailed explanation.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot walk a long distance and carry heavy things," she
said. 
</P>
