<HEADLINE> Experts Call for Less Cashmere Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese experts have warned that
the excessive export of cashmere causes great losses to the
country, as the price gap between raw material and finished
products is huge.
</P>
<P>
China produced 5,000 tons of cashmere in 1995, more than half
of the world's total, according to a recent report in "China's
Textile Industry News."
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 tons of cashmere is exported to the developed
nations each year at low price, the report noted.
</P>
<P>
Experts urged the Chinese government to quicken the pace of the
legislation on cashmere exports.
</P>
<P>
China has more than 2,000 small and medium-size cashmere
processing factories, which need some 6,000 tons of cashmere for
raw material and have an annual production capacity of four
million cashmere sweaters, scarves and garments, the report said.
