<HEADLINE> hke-Crimes Increase in Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 12, 955 crimes
were recorded in Mongolia in the past seven months, the local
newspaper, People's Right, reported today.
</P>
<P>
Of the offenses, robberies accounted for 56 percent. Sixty-five
percent of the criminals were jobless or students unable to attend
school. Seven percent were under the age of 17.
</P>
<P>
By early August, Mongolia's unemployed had increased to 52,000,
up 6,900 from the beginning of the year. Among the unemployed,
14.5 percent were jobless for the first time. 
