<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) left here today for Seychelles after a
five-day friendly visit to strengthen bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by Madam Huan Guoying, Deputy Minister of
the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central
Committee, met with National Chairman of the ruling Kenya African
National Union (KANU) Wilson Ndolo Ayah and other KANU officials
for talks on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ayah conveyed best wishes of Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi,
who is also the KANU president, to the CPC delegation, saying
President Moi hoped to enhance the cooperative ties between the
ruling parties of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said President Moi was satisfied with the existing
cooperation between KANU and CPC, noting that the recent visits
to China by the KANU delegation had "cemented contact between the
two parties" and resulted in Kenya's better understanding of
China.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Huan said she was happy with the cooperation between
KANU and the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
She appreciated Kenya for its consistent support to China by
insisting on the "One-China policy" as well as in other
international affairs including the human rights issues which
have been used by some Western countries to oppose China.
</P>
<P>
Huan, who had arrived in Kenya on Saturday following her visit
to Eritrea, also made a courtesy call on Kenya's Vice-President
George Saitoti on Monday who is also the KANU vice-president.
</P>
<P>
She conveyed the kind regards of Chinese President Jiang
Zemin, who is also the CPC chairman, to President Moi and
Vice-President Saitoti.
</P>
<P>
Saitoti said the Kenya tour of the CPC delegation "fully
manifested the friendship between Kenya and China", reaffirming
that China is "a true friend" of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Seychelles will be the last leg of a two-week three-nation
African tour of the CPC delegation. 
