<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Chemical Fertilizer Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnam Chemical Corporation
(VCC) has turned out more than 800,000 tonnes of chemical
fertilizers of various kinds so far this year, up by 10 percent
compared to the same period last year, local press said today.
</P>
<P>
The corporation, the main provider of chemical fertilizers for
the country, is now operating four plants with a combined annual
capacity of 820,000 tonnes of phosphorous fertilizer per year and
another plant which produces 110,000 tonnes of nitrogenous
fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
These establishments meet 70-80 percent of domestic demand for
phosphate and 10 percent for nitrogenous fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
To satisfy the growing demand for chemical fertilizers, VCC has
carried out a plan to raise the total capacity of phosphate plants
to 1.2 million tonnes per year and build another plant with an
annual capacity of 350,000 tonnes.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, the Ha Bac Nitrogenous Fertilizer Company is
installing a new production line with a design capacity of 280,000
tonnes per year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two more nitrogenous fertilizer plants are expected
to be put into operation by the end of 1998, and an npk fertilizer
plant with a designed capacity of 350,000 tonnes per year is to be
built in Ho Chi Minh city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
