<HEADLINE> Fierce Fighting Lasts Overnight in Grozny </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A fierce fighting between Russian
forces and Chechen rebels lasted overnight from midnight to 5:00
a.m. local time (2000-0100 GMT) in the center and other districts
of the capital city Grozny.
</P>
<P>
According to Interfax news agency reports today, the combat
began when Chechen separatists fired at government buildings in
the center of the city and the Russian Federation Army returned
shots immediately.
</P>
<P>
The rebels started a new attempt to storm the city's government
buildings at about 07:00 a.m. (0300 GMT), against which Russian
military helicopters launched missiles to attack the rebels'
positions around the town of Argun, to the east of Grozny.
</P>
<P>
During the daytime of Tuesday, hundreds of Chechen rebels had
assaulted the capital city and two other towns of Chechnya,
leaving 36 soldiers and policemen dead, and 136 wounded on the
Russian side by 9:00 p.m. the same day.
</P>
<P>
Rebel spokesman Movladi Udugov said in an interview with
Russian Television that the assault was in retaliation for a month
of Russian bombardments of their villages and strongholds in the
southern mountains. But he declared that the Chechens still
wanted to return to peace talks and end the vicious 20-month war.
</P>
<P>
The fighting thwarted Russian attempts to hold peace talks with
the Chechen rebels and embarrassed Boris Yeltsin, the re-elected
Russian president, as he was preparing for his inauguration on
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
