<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysian Air Force Chief to Retire on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Chief of the Royal Malaysian
Air Force (RMAF) Lieut. Gen. Abdul Ghani Aziz will retire on
Friday after his 32 years' service in the armed forces, Malaysia's
official news agency Bernama reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that his successor is yet to be announced.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Ghani, 52, started as a cadet officer in the Royal
Military College on August 10, 1964, and received his commission
on September 13 in the same year. He was promoted to the rank of
lieutenant general in 1993.
</P>
<P>
He was the first air force chief trained locally and also the
first graduate of the Malaysian Armed Forces Staff College to head
one of the three services in the country's armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Ghani is described as a versatile officer who can fly not
only ordinary aircraft and helicopters but also fighter jets.
</P>
<P>
The report said that several national awards had been conferred
upon him for his outstanding services while other countries,
including Jordan and Indonesia, also conferred honors on him.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
