has triggered an outcry from French public opinion. The abortion
of one of the twins, called "selective abortion" or "embryonic
reduction," can be risky for the other embryo. The 28-year-old
single mother called "Miss B" has already had one child and said
she could not afford three. The well-known French medical
professor Jean-Francois Mattei described the abortion as
"monstrous."
</P>
<P>
-- The European Union will prolong its mission in the Bosnian
city of Mostar after the Croats agreed to join its municipality. But
a reunification of the city is still not guaranteed. 
