<HEADLINE> Hubei Boosts Export-oriented Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province has
pledged to form an export-oriented economic pattern by the end of
this century.
</P>
<P>
Hubei will concentrate on building a comprehensive industrial
base featuring iron and steel, automobile and building materials,
and also an export-oriented farm produce base, a power-generating
base, a high-tech industrial base, and a foreign trade base.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the province's foreign trade will reach
7.5 billion US dollars in the year 2000, and use foreign capital
totalling seven billion US dollars in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
Located along the middle reaches of the Yangtze River, Hubei is
known as the country's largest interior transport and
telecommunications hub.
</P>
<P>
Its import and export output value in the first half of this
year totalled 137 million US dollars, and it used 270 million US
dollars during this period.
</P>
<P>
Hubei ranks among the first in the country in the production of
grain, cotton and edible oil, second in automobiles, and fifth in
steel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
