<HEADLINE> Collection of Ancient Classics to Be Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua)-- A collection of ancient classic
poems and essays written during the Song Dynasty (960-1279 a.d.)
is to be published soon.
</P>
<P>
The ten-volume collection was written by Zhu Xi (1130-1200), a
famous scholar in the Song Dynasty, who was an ancient idealist
and a follower of the renowned philosopher Confucius.
</P>
<P>
The series will be published in October by the Sichuan
Education Press. The collection includes a vast accumulation of
Zhu Xi's poems and essays, which cover a variety of topics.
</P>
<P>
During their research for the project, editors studied hundreds
of thousands of ancient and modern works relating to Zhu's
writings, particularly those in the Song Dynasty.
</P>
<P>
All of Zhu's previously-published collections were reviewed and
revised after careful comparison, identification and proofreading.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that the collection's publication will promote
further understanding of the theories of the ancient Chinese
philosophy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
