<HEADLINE> Yunnan's Scenic Spots Attracting Large Number of Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- If you're looking for loads of
spectacular scenery in a single spot, try China's southwestern
Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The province now has ten state-level scenic areas, 48
provincial-level scenic areas, and six at the city or county
level. The figure takes the lead in China to account for 12
percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The combined coverage of Yunnan's scenic areas stands at 13,000
square kilometers, representing 3.3 percent of the province's
total area. Statistics show that China's scenic areas cover a
total of 96,000 sq km, accounting for one percent of the country's
territory.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan's snow mountains, primitive forests, grasslands, rivers,
lakes, and ethnic folklore are attracting an increasing number of
domestic and foreign tourists. 
