<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Get Grants From EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will receive grants
worth 140 million US Dollars from the European Union in the next
three and half years under the Lome Convention, the local daily
Herald reported today.
</P>
<P>
The grants are Zimbabwe's share of programmable resources
under the eighth European development fund which was agreed as
part of the protocol signed in Mauritius in November last year.
</P>
<P>
This covered period until 2000 and constituted a significant
increase in real terms over the previous allocation.
</P>
<P>
The grants form the core of the EU programme but do not take
account of probable additional grant resources such as structural
adjustment support, food aid, emergency assistance and
co-financing with NGOs. 
</P>
