<HEADLINE> Pete Sampras Beats Hlasek in ATP Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Pete Sampras needed
only 57 minutes to fight off unseeded Jakob Hlasek of Switzerland
6-3, 6-4 on Tuesday, sailing into the third round of the 2.2
million U.S. dollars ATP Championship in Mason, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
But Jim Courier was not as fortunate as his fellow American
Sampras, overcoming a hard-hitting Greg Rusedski of Britain 6-7
(3-7), 6-3, 6-4 after two hours and 12 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, also the world's top-ranked player, said he was
pleased with his performance after having taken five weeks off
since his quarterfinal loss at Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
The unseeded Rusedski, who eliminated Denmark's Kenneth Carlsen
on Monday, shocked Courier with his powerful serves in the first
set of the second round match, which took 56 minutes and was
forced to a tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
But the eighth seeded Courier battled back to win the next two
sets with aggressive service and crafty groundstrokes as
Rusedski's serve faded.
</P>
<P>
Courier, the world's eighth-ranked player, has beaten Rusedski
in all three encounters. 
