<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Creatures From the Deep Photographed in Tianchi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- If they're lucky, tourists to
Tianchi Lake, a famous scenic spot in northeast China, can look
out from the peak of Changbaishan mountain and see mysterious
animals swimming in the lake below.
</P>
<P>
Some have compared the creatures from the deep to dinosaurs or
buffalo. Others say the strange beasts look like huge iron pots.
</P>
<P>
On July 14, photographer Wang Ying captured on film the
activities of four of the unidentified critters swimming in the
lake.
</P>
<P>
Chai Jingguo, head of the Changbaishan Tianchi Mysterious
Animal Research Association, said that Wang has been monitoring
the things since last summer.
</P>
<P>
Early that morning, Wang went to the lake's nearby Tianwen Peak
and waited for them to appear. At 8:30, he spotted several black
figures moving in the water. He counted four, floating and diving
leisurely, sometimes splashing waves one or two meters high.
</P>
<P>
They swam for several minutes and returned underwater. Wang
photographed their actions for 30 seconds.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 tourists witnessed their appearance, and said
they had never seen such creatures before.
</P>
<P>
The research association is a non-governmental organization,
founded several years ago by Chinese government officials, tourism
officers and journalists, and a number of people from South Korea,
Japan and other countries.
</P>
<P>
Last August, the association and the Administration Bureau of
the Jilin Changbaishan Natural Reserves jointly set up a station
to observe the mysterious animals, and invited Wang to participate
in a professional capacity.
</P>
<P>
Tianchi is a border lake between China and the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea. It has a water surface area of 10
sq. km. and an average water depth of 204 meters,
</P>
<P>
It is the largest volcano lake and the deepest mountain lake in
China.
</P>
<P>
Many people doubted the existence of the mysterious creatures,
though local government records showed sightings of unidentified
animals at the beginning of this century.
</P>
<P>
In past decades, hundreds of people claim to have seen the
strange creatures in Tianchi. Recently, people have photographed
the animals, but their shots were taken from the top of the
mountain, more than 1,000 meters above the lake, and only small
portions of the animals' bodies were visible.
</P>
<P>
Chai said that according to the historical records and
tourists' descriptions, the animals are most likely to appear
between June and September.
</P>
<P>
The association plans to organize a scientific inspection tour
in August to explore the myth of the strange creatures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960807.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
