<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province is
focusing on improving infrastructure and developing
export-oriented economy along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
There are 1,200 overseas-funded enterprises in the province,
which has four cities and four prefectures along the banks of
China's longest river, a survey showed.
</P>
<P>
During the first six months of this year, the river section
shipped more than 300,000 tons of cargoes, an increase of 150
percent over the same 1995 period.
</P>
<P>
The province has built a number of key infrastructure projects,
such as the Tongling Yangtze River Bridge, the Hefei-Wuhu
Expressway and the Hefei-Tongling Highway.
</P>
<P>
