<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wheat Yield in Bulgaria Drops Drastically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The wheat yield of Bulgaria this
year has been the lowest over the past ten years, a senior
official said today.
</P>
<P>
Dimo. Wzinov, vice minister of the Agriculture Department, told
a news conference that the wheat yield this year dropped
drastically, which is the first time that Bulgaria has experienced
for ten years.
</P>
<P>
The yield is expected to reach at most 1.9 million tons this
year, accounting for only 35 percent of that in 1990, according to
the ministry. Little fertilizer, bad climate and the increase in
deserted land are responsible for the serious situation.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria needs 1.6 million tons of wheat this year. The
government can only purchase 1 million tons from the farmers and
the country have no choice but to import the rest 0.6 million tons
of wheat from the United States and Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
