<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan President Julio
Maria Sanguinetti inaugurated here today the Conference of Latin
American Port Authorities that will congregate representatives
from 24 countries of the region for 3 days.
</P>
<P>
Organized by Uruguay's National Port Administration (ANP), the
meeting will focuse its attention on topics such as international
trade, the modernization of ports, new services, customs and
relations among Southern Cone Common Market (Mercosur) ports.
</P>
