<HEADLINE> 2 Thai Banks to Form Joint Ventures in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Thai banks have agreed in
principle to form joint ventures with two Myanmar private banks,
the New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar Minister for Finance and Revenue Brig. Gen. Win Tin
made the disclosure here Tuesday at a signing ceremony of a
memorandum of understanding between Bangkok-based Loxley Myanmar
Co. Ltd. and a Myanmar private bank -- Asia Wealth Bank Ltd. -- on
issuing the Smart Card in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture banks are to be formed between the Thai
Farmers Bank and Myanmar's Asia Wealth Bank and between the Thai
Siam City Bank and Myanmar's May Flower Bank, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The eventual formation of the first two joint venture banks
between foreign banks and Myanmar private banks signals Myanmar's
entry into the second phase of its financial reform, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official statistics, in the first phase
of the reform, the Myanmar government has granted the operation of
20 private banks in the country and the establishment of 39
foreign bank representative offices as of the end of March this
year, including six Thai banks.  
</P>
