<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Green Peace Opposes U.S. Radioactive Waste Dump in Texas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Green Peace, an
international environmental pressure group, today protested
U.S. dumping of radioactive waste in the state of Texas, which
borders on Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Lopez, a spokesman for the group, said the toxic waste
dump in Sierra Blanca, Texas, poses a threat to the health of both
U.S. and Mexican citizens.
</P>
<P>
The radioactive waste dump is only 32 kilometers from Mexican
territory and therefore could affect aquifers, he said.
</P>
<P>
Green Peace members today gathered before the main gate of the
U.S. Embassy in Mexico to protest over the dumping of the
radioactive waste. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
