<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Swiss Joint Venture Set up in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua)-- ABB High Voltage Switchgear Co Ltd
Beijing made its debut yesterday, aiming to produce high voltage
switchgears to satisfy the growing demand for electrical equipment
in China' power industry.
</P>
<P>
The $25 million company is jointly funded by international
electrical engineering group ABB and Beijing Switchgear
Factory(BSF). ABB holds 60 per cent of the shares and BSF holds
the remaining 40 per cent, today's China Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The company is the first joint venture in the switchgear
industry in China. A switchgear is a type of equipment used for
transmitting and distributing electricity.
</P>
<P>
The company will specialize in design, engineering,
manufacturing, sales and service of electrical equipment for high
voltage switchgears.
</P>
<P>
ABB, headquartered in Zurich, is one of the world's largest
electrical engineering firms, with global operations comprising
more than 1,000 companies in over 140 countries.
</P>
<P>
ABB's relationship with China dates back to the beginning of
the century, when it supplied the country with a steam boiler in
1907 .
</P>
<P>
So far, ABB has set up nine offices across China and
established 14 joint ventures with local partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
