<HEADLINE> Beijing Tax Man Moves in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-funded enterprises and
overseas individuals in Beijing should pay part of their taxes to
branches of the Beijing Local Taxation Bureau instead of the city's
State taxation bureau starting from September 1, "China Daily"
reports today.
</P>
<P>
The taxes, including business tax, individual income tax,
resource tax, land value increment tax, urban real estate tax,
vehicle and ship license tax, stamp tax and butchery tax, are now
collected by the State taxation bureau.
</P>
<P>
Since the country's taxation reform in 1994, the levying of the
above taxes paid by domestic enterprises and individuals has been
conducted by local taxation bureaux. However, the same taxes from
overseas payers had remained to be levied by the state taxation
bureaux in some cities, the paper says.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Beijing Local Taxation Bureau reminded the
overseas payers of the changes and reminded them to contact one of
the bureau's 22 branches for tax declaration and registration
before September 1 for a smooth transition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
