<HEADLINE> Capriati Advances in Du Maurier Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- American Jennifer Capriati
advanced to the second round of the 1.3 million U.S. dollars du
Maurier Open women's tennis tournament with a 6-4, 6-2 win over
11th-seeded Irina Spirlea of Romania in Montreal, Canada, on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the 20-year-old Capriati's first win since March. She
will take on fellow American Lori McNeil in the second round, a
6-3, 6-7 (7-5), 7-5 winner over Italy's Silvia Farina.
</P>
<P>
Capriati became the youngest du Maurier Open champion ever at
age 15, when she won in Toronto in 1991. But she played only one
match in two and half years following a shoplifting incident and
her drug rehabilitation in 1993.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Virginia Ruano-Pascual of Spain ousted 1986
champion and 14th-seeded Helena Sukova of the Czech Republic 7-5,
3-6, 6-4 and Rennae Stubbs of Australia downed 12th-seeded
Katarina Habsudova of Slovakia 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seeded Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria outplayed American
Lisa Raymond 6-4, 6-3, while Mary Pierce of France fought back
from one set down to beat Russia's Elena Makarova 2-6, 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded American Monica Seles plays later Tuesday. 
</P>
