<HEADLINE> More Foreign Tourists Visit Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The number of foreign
tourists visiting Panama rose eight percent to 160,600 in the
first half of this year over the same period last year, the
Panamanian Institute of Tourism (PIT) said today.
</P>
<P>
Most visitors came in February, March and June, a PIT report
said.
</P>
<P>
Overall last year, 388,000 tourists visited Panama and spent
243.5 million U.S. dollars. But the government hopes that by 2002,
the number of tourists will increase four fold to 1.6 million.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian hotels reported an overall occupancy rate of 54.2
percent up to June this year, with the rate for first-class hotels
at 71.6 percent and for second-class hotels at 35.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, 388,137 tourists entered Panama and spent 243.5
million balboas (243.5 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
