<HEADLINE> Former Tanzanian PM Elected Judge of ITLS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Joseph Warioba, former
Prime Minister of Tanzania, has been elected judge of the
International Tribunal of the Law of the Sea (ITLS).
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here today, the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs and International Co-operation said that the election was
conducted on August 1 in New York by the conference of states
parties to the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea.
</P>
<P>
Warioba joins a panel of 21 independent members elected from
among persons enjoying the highest reputation for fairness and
integrity and of recognized competence in the field of the law of
the sea.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that amongst 36 aspirants, Africa presented
10 candidates and only 5 of whom were successful, namely the
candidates from Tanzania, Tunisia, Ghana, Cameroon and Senegal.
</P>
<P>
The tribunal is due to convene for its first session on
October 1 for administrative purposes including the election of
its president, the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
