<HEADLINE> S. African Olympic Team Returns Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The South African Olympic
team returned home this evening to a rousing welcome from a
singing, chanting multiracial crowd of 2,000 at Johannesburg
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
A banner claiming "to us you are all worth gold" caught the
mood of the welcome as the smiling athletes stepped onto a
balcony in the airport's international concourse to accept the
adulation of the young and old.
</P>
<P>
However, the biggest cheers were apparently reserved for
swimming double gold medalist Penny Heyns and the crowd's
undoubted favorite, the first black South African Olympic gold
medalist Josiah Thugwane, men's marathon winner at Atlanta
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The team is officially welcomed back by Gauteng Provincial
Government Premier Tokyo Sexwale at an international media
conference at the airport.
</P>
<P>
While addressing the team, Sexwale said the whole South Africa
is proud of their achievements at Atlanta, which had caused
tears of joy in "many of those who will admit it".
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, presidential spokesman Parks Mankahlana said
the president, could not personally welcome home the team due to
previous engagements, has been "overwhelmed" by the achievements
of the South Africans in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
The South African Olympic team won 3 gold medals, one silver
medal and one bronze medal, ranking 27th in final medals table
among the 197 teams participating in the Atlanta games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
