<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Meets British Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan president Yoweri
Museveni said today that the government has given its first
priority to the eradication of poverty of Uganda by the maximum
utilisation of available land.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with British Minister for Foreign and
Commonwealth Affairs Boroness Lynda Chalker, Museveni said that
Uganda will take steps to modernize its agriculture and to ensure
a conductive atmosphere for private investment.
