<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Edged Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street turned
mostly higher today, with the Dow Jones industrial average adding
21.83 to 5,696.11.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with its volume totaling 347.23
million shares, higher than 303.77 million in Monday's sluggish
session.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE's composite index rose 0.84 to 353.65, and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock index rose 2.15 to 662.38.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 8.33 to 1,128.86, and the
American Stock Exchange's market value index rose 0.15 to 548.74.
</P>
<P>
There was no new economic data today to supplement last week's
encouraging indications on inflation, and there was little
corporate news to steer trading as investors focused on the start
of this week's three-day auction of new U.S. Treasury debt.
</P>
<P>
But the first phase, this afternoon's auction of 19 billion
U.S. dollar in three-year notes, did not erode last week's gains
in bond prices or send interest rates higher.
</P>
<P>
The yield on the 30-year Treasury bond actually eased further.
</P>
</TEXT>
