<HEADLINE> Athens Welcomes Olympic Champions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Fresh from its best performance in
100 years, the Greek Olympic team returned to Athens this evening,
greeted by tens of thousands of Athenians, who lined a route from
the airport to the Central Panathenian Stadium, where celebrations
in their honor were held well into the night.
</P>
<P>
Flag-waving crowds cheered the athletes, who displayed their
medals to adoring fans, while riding atop military jeeps.
</P>
<P>
During the Atlanta games, Greek weightlifters Pyros Dimas and
Akakios Kakhiashvili won gold medals, along with Yiannis
Melissanidis in gymnastics and Nikos Kaklamanakis in the men's
yachting event. Three more weightlifters won silver medals along
with Niki Bakoyianni in the women's high jump.
</P>
<P>
Before arriving at the Panathenian stadium, the motorcade ended
at the Temple of Zeus, where the eight medalists were awarded the
"Gold Medal of Honor" by Athens Mayor Dimitris Avramopoulos.
</P>
<P>
All the Olympic finalists, in the first eight positions in
their respective events, then proceeded to the packed 80,000-seat
stadium on foot.
</P>
<P>
Fireworks subsequently lit up the warm Athenian sky, as the
athletes entered the marble stadium, greeted by Greek President
Kostis Stephanopulos, Prime Minister Costas Simitis, ministers and
all of the nation's political leadership.
</P>
<P>
In his address, Simitis said, "Your victory for all of us is a
great lesson, showing that nothing is conquered without toil, that
nothing is won without sacrifices, that nothing is consolidated
without effort, that nothing is ensured without outdoing
ourselves." 
</P>
</TEXT>
